-- Motorola buys video encoding company Modulus Video
-- 
-- Thu May 17, 2007 8:26am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/05/17/us-motorola-modulus-idUSWEN820020070517

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Motorola Inc. MOT.N said on Thursday it will buy Modulus Video Inc., a privately held video encoding company, for an undisclosed amount. 

 Modulus Video does encoding that enables the delivery of video content in the IPTV, cable, broadcast and satellite marketplace. Modulus Video has partnered with Motorola for more than two years. Motorola said the purchase will complement its recent acquisitions of Broadbus, Kreatel, Tut Systems and Netopia.